1
00:00:01,835 --> 00:00:04,087
- [grunts]
- [woman] <i>Geez! You again?</i>

2
00:00:04,170 --> 00:00:06,381
[man] <i>It seems like</i>
<i>we keep running into each other.</i>

3
00:00:06,464 --> 00:00:08,258
- [woman] <i>Are you stalking me?</i>
- Of course not.

4
00:00:08,341 --> 00:00:11,511
[woman] <i>Well, I wouldn't mind if you did.</i>

5
00:00:13,179 --> 00:00:14,597
[Jamilah] <i>Good thing I found it.</i>

6
00:00:14,681 --> 00:00:15,640
<i>I didn't know that toy</i>
<i>was so special to you.</i>

7
00:00:15,724 --> 00:00:17,183
[Marcus] <i>It was my brother's.</i>

8
00:00:17,267 --> 00:00:19,394
You really love your brother, don't you?

9
00:00:19,477 --> 00:00:23,356
Gabriel is very lucky
to have a brother like you

10
00:00:23,440 --> 00:00:24,607
who loves him so much.

11
00:00:28,069 --> 00:00:31,698
[Marcus]
<i>The authorities ruled it an accident.</i>

12
00:00:31,781 --> 00:00:33,450
<i>But was it really just an accident?</i>

13
00:00:33,533 --> 00:00:35,869
<i>Were you the one who caused the explosion?</i>

14
00:00:35,952 --> 00:00:39,247
<i>Are you the reason my brother is gone?</i>

15
00:00:39,330 --> 00:00:41,374
Jalil, wait!

16
00:00:41,458 --> 00:00:42,959
I'm coming with you.

17
00:00:43,042 --> 00:00:44,836
[woman] <i>She doesn't have parents anymore.</i>

18
00:00:46,463 --> 00:00:48,423
<i>Maybe you can take her with you.</i>

19
00:00:51,009 --> 00:00:53,511
<i>Felix, what is this?</i>
<i>Are we really doing the right thing?</i>

20
00:00:54,137 --> 00:00:55,847
<i>- Why are children getting involved?</i>
- [gunshot]

21
00:00:55,930 --> 00:00:57,849
[Felix] <i>Don't say that!</i>
<i>Do you know what could happen to you…</i>

22
00:00:57,932 --> 00:00:59,559
- What's wrong with you?
- …if General hears you?

23
00:00:59,642 --> 00:01:00,977
- Listen to me!
- Let me go!

24
00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:02,228
- [slaps]
- Enough!

25
00:01:02,312 --> 00:01:05,398
You have no right
to question General's orders!

26
00:01:05,482 --> 00:01:06,733
Dad is not God!

27
00:01:06,816 --> 00:01:07,942
But I'm afraid of him.

28
00:01:08,026 --> 00:01:09,486
[Felix] <i>If you still want to live,</i>

29
00:01:09,569 --> 00:01:13,156
<i>never let General hear your doubts.</i>

30
00:01:13,990 --> 00:01:19,454
[theme music playing]

31
00:01:30,131 --> 00:01:31,216
Sitti?

32
00:01:32,258 --> 00:01:34,594
Do you remember everything I told you?

33
00:01:34,677 --> 00:01:36,221
Yes, Jalil.

34
00:01:36,304 --> 00:01:38,848
Oh, right. You're not Jalil.

35
00:01:38,932 --> 00:01:40,058
Who are you?

36
00:01:40,141 --> 00:01:43,645
[tongue clicks] Be a good girl, okay?

37
00:01:43,728 --> 00:01:46,439
Don't give Jamilah a hard time.

38
00:01:47,816 --> 00:01:50,026
[in Tausug] Thank you, Jalil.

39
00:01:50,110 --> 00:01:54,405
[in Tagalog] Back on the island,
whenever I felt sad,

40
00:01:54,989 --> 00:01:57,492
I prayed that

41
00:01:57,575 --> 00:02:01,704
I could see you and Jamilah again.

42
00:02:01,788 --> 00:02:06,709
I'm so glad Allah listened to my prayers.

43
00:02:09,295 --> 00:02:13,258
I thought He had forgotten about us

44
00:02:13,341 --> 00:02:15,552
after what happened.

45
00:02:15,635 --> 00:02:16,928
Sitti…

46
00:02:17,804 --> 00:02:19,514
Listen to me, alright?

47
00:02:21,391 --> 00:02:23,685
Allah is always listening to us.

48
00:02:24,269 --> 00:02:27,480
What happened to our community was tragic.

49
00:02:27,564 --> 00:02:32,152
It was caused by greedy, evil people.

50
00:02:32,986 --> 00:02:36,698
But that doesn't mean
Allah has forsaken us.

51
00:02:38,658 --> 00:02:40,160
He wants us

52
00:02:41,035 --> 00:02:44,706
to be strong for each other.

53
00:02:45,707 --> 00:02:48,251
At the end of the day,
good will always prevail.

54
00:02:49,252 --> 00:02:52,630
Have faith, Sitti.

55
00:02:53,339 --> 00:02:57,468
Always choose kindness,
even when it's hard.

56
00:02:58,094 --> 00:02:59,929
For your loved ones.

57
00:03:00,013 --> 00:03:05,518
[pensive music playing]

58
00:03:08,855 --> 00:03:10,648
Okay, well…

59
00:03:10,732 --> 00:03:12,567
Jamilah's here.

60
00:03:14,277 --> 00:03:15,653
Sitti.

61
00:03:15,737 --> 00:03:18,865
Do you promise you'll be a good girl?

62
00:03:18,948 --> 00:03:20,450
[sniffles] Yes.

63
00:03:20,533 --> 00:03:21,993
Bye, Jalil.

64
00:03:22,076 --> 00:03:24,913
I promise to be a good girl.

65
00:03:24,996 --> 00:03:26,789
[chuckles softly] I believe you.

66
00:03:28,708 --> 00:03:30,877
- Take care, Sitti.
- Yes.

67
00:03:31,711 --> 00:03:33,129
Go on.

68
00:03:33,212 --> 00:03:36,591
[hopeful music playing]

69
00:03:37,175 --> 00:03:38,092
- Sitti!
- [car door closes]

70
00:03:41,054 --> 00:03:42,472
Sitti!

71
00:03:42,555 --> 00:03:47,685
[hopeful music continues]

72
00:03:51,606 --> 00:03:52,857
Come on. Let's go!

73
00:03:52,941 --> 00:03:56,694
[hopeful music continues]

74
00:03:58,112 --> 00:04:00,448
This is where you'll live. [chuckles]

75
00:04:01,574 --> 00:04:04,285
- These are our neighbors!
- Wow!

76
00:04:04,369 --> 00:04:07,455
It's beautiful here, Jamilah!

77
00:04:11,042 --> 00:04:12,669
What's the matter?

78
00:04:13,461 --> 00:04:15,213
[inhales, sighs]

79
00:04:19,676 --> 00:04:20,843
Nothing.

80
00:04:21,928 --> 00:04:23,680
You know…

81
00:04:26,182 --> 00:04:28,851
I'm so glad you're here.

82
00:04:30,019 --> 00:04:32,605
I haven't seen you in so long.

83
00:04:32,689 --> 00:04:35,316
I missed you so much.

84
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:37,235
You're always on my mind.

85
00:04:38,361 --> 00:04:40,655
I'm glad you're here now.

86
00:04:41,322 --> 00:04:46,411
I miss our community.

87
00:04:47,495 --> 00:04:48,705
Don't cry.

88
00:04:49,664 --> 00:04:50,957
[Sitti sniffles]

89
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:53,084
I missed you too, Jamilah.

90
00:04:53,167 --> 00:04:55,044
That's why I went with Jalil,

91
00:04:55,128 --> 00:04:57,922
because I really miss you. [sniffles]

92
00:04:59,382 --> 00:05:00,425
Come here.

93
00:05:00,508 --> 00:05:04,804
[gentle music playing]

94
00:05:04,887 --> 00:05:05,972
[sighs deeply]

95
00:05:08,182 --> 00:05:09,392
Alright.

96
00:05:09,475 --> 00:05:13,187
I want you to meet someone, okay?
Let's go.

97
00:05:14,105 --> 00:05:15,273
Come.

98
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:20,028
Watch your step.

99
00:05:20,111 --> 00:05:23,948
[stirring music playing]

100
00:05:24,032 --> 00:05:25,241
Come in.

101
00:05:27,785 --> 00:05:29,078
Auntie Norhana, Uncle Omar.

102
00:05:29,746 --> 00:05:31,706
- Mm.
- Is this Sitti?

103
00:05:31,789 --> 00:05:33,750
- Yes.
- [in Arabic] Oh my goodness.

104
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:35,543
[in Tagalog] You're adorable, sweetie.

105
00:05:35,626 --> 00:05:37,795
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you, Sitti!

106
00:05:37,879 --> 00:05:43,301
[in Tagalog] Sitti,
meet Auntie Norhana and Uncle Omar.

107
00:05:43,384 --> 00:05:47,346
They'll look after you when I'm at work.

108
00:05:47,430 --> 00:05:48,681
[Jamilah chuckles softly]

109
00:05:48,765 --> 00:05:51,893
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you,
Auntie Norhana, Uncle Omar.

110
00:05:51,976 --> 00:05:53,728
[giggles]

111
00:05:56,522 --> 00:05:59,317
[clapping]

112
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,444
[applause, cheering]

113
00:06:01,527 --> 00:06:05,323
- Yes!
- Congratulations!

114
00:06:05,907 --> 00:06:07,825
You've gone viral again! [laughs]

115
00:06:08,409 --> 00:06:09,619
Congratulations, brother.

116
00:06:09,702 --> 00:06:10,912
Whoo!

117
00:06:10,995 --> 00:06:12,997
You're incredible, sir! Congrats!

118
00:06:14,832 --> 00:06:15,666
Nice work, sir.

119
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:17,335
Congrats, sir.

120
00:06:18,211 --> 00:06:19,921
[Felix] Solid win, Sir Marcus.

121
00:06:20,713 --> 00:06:21,798
Congratulations!

122
00:06:22,381 --> 00:06:25,802
[applause, cheers continue]

123
00:06:27,428 --> 00:06:29,097
[Felix] Great job.

124
00:06:29,180 --> 00:06:33,476
Marcus Reyes,
the leader of Task Force Alpha,

125
00:06:33,559 --> 00:06:35,269
came to our island?

126
00:06:35,353 --> 00:06:37,647
Ramli, what did he want?

127
00:06:37,730 --> 00:06:41,692
He had a lot of questions
about what happened that night.

128
00:06:42,568 --> 00:06:45,822
He was looking for answers.
He was able to confirm that

129
00:06:45,905 --> 00:06:48,199
a different group opened fire on us.

130
00:06:48,825 --> 00:06:53,204
He discovered spent bullet casings
on the adjacent mountain.

131
00:06:55,081 --> 00:06:58,584
He believes your father is innocent.

132
00:06:59,961 --> 00:07:01,879
He's gathering evidence to prove it.

133
00:07:01,963 --> 00:07:04,799
So I took him to where
our weapons are buried.

134
00:07:06,551 --> 00:07:07,885
Did anyone see him?

135
00:07:07,969 --> 00:07:09,095
No.

136
00:07:09,178 --> 00:07:12,432
Just me, Tanaon, and Sir Harold.

137
00:07:14,809 --> 00:07:17,311
He wanted to apologize to the community,

138
00:07:17,395 --> 00:07:19,647
but in the end, he didn’t.

139
00:07:19,730 --> 00:07:22,442
He let our people mourn in peace.

140
00:07:22,525 --> 00:07:25,611
[morose music playing]

141
00:07:27,363 --> 00:07:28,990
What are you thinking?

142
00:07:29,782 --> 00:07:32,535
I'm just wondering…

143
00:07:32,618 --> 00:07:34,954
why he left Sir Harold here

144
00:07:35,037 --> 00:07:37,415
after finding out he was alive.

145
00:07:37,498 --> 00:07:42,920
Why did he choose to entrust his friend
to people who hate him?

146
00:07:43,921 --> 00:07:45,381
That means…

147
00:07:46,132 --> 00:07:49,844
Marcus knows Harold is safer here with you

148
00:07:51,512 --> 00:07:53,806
than with his colleagues back in Manila.

149
00:07:55,516 --> 00:07:56,726
Ramli…

150
00:07:58,227 --> 00:07:59,729
[in Tausug] Be careful.

151
00:08:03,399 --> 00:08:05,318
[applauding, cheering]

152
00:08:05,401 --> 00:08:07,195
Thank you very much, everyone.

153
00:08:07,278 --> 00:08:09,447
Thank you very much, but…

154
00:08:09,530 --> 00:08:11,491
I can't do this alone.

155
00:08:12,450 --> 00:08:13,868
This was a team effort.

156
00:08:13,951 --> 00:08:17,955
This mission was accomplished
because of all of us.

157
00:08:18,789 --> 00:08:19,707
- [officer 1] Wooh!
- [officer 2] Yes!

158
00:08:19,790 --> 00:08:25,838
[applauding, cheering]

159
00:08:27,381 --> 00:08:29,133
- Reyes…
- [applauding]

160
00:08:29,217 --> 00:08:31,594
Congratulations. I saw the news.

161
00:08:32,178 --> 00:08:34,055
It's good you were able to save the child.

162
00:08:35,389 --> 00:08:36,390
So you're back.

163
00:08:37,850 --> 00:08:39,018
What did you do?

164
00:08:40,394 --> 00:08:42,647
Uh, I just took care of something.

165
00:08:46,025 --> 00:08:47,193
Are you okay?

166
00:08:48,402 --> 00:08:50,655
Uh, it's nothing, just a graze.

167
00:08:52,740 --> 00:08:54,867
You, what happened there?

168
00:08:58,329 --> 00:08:59,247
Just a graze too.

169
00:09:00,373 --> 00:09:03,417
I'm glad we're finally on the same side…

170
00:09:03,501 --> 00:09:04,877
Agent Reyes.

171
00:09:08,714 --> 00:09:10,841
- Me too…
- [applauding]

172
00:09:10,925 --> 00:09:12,552
Major Allan Espina.

173
00:09:12,635 --> 00:09:15,012
[applauding, cheering]

174
00:09:18,724 --> 00:09:22,687
["Maninindigan" by Marko Rudio playing]

175
00:09:27,275 --> 00:09:30,861
[applauding]

176
00:09:35,366 --> 00:09:36,534
- Hey, girl.
- Hmm?

177
00:09:36,617 --> 00:09:39,537
You thought I didn't see it
last night, huh?

178
00:09:39,620 --> 00:09:42,290
You were talking
to Dr. Teresa's handsome son.

179
00:09:42,957 --> 00:09:44,875
- Hey, you know what--
- Oh, come on!

180
00:09:44,959 --> 00:09:46,502
You're so malicious-minded!

181
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:50,798
He was just thanking me
because I found what he was looking for.

182
00:09:51,591 --> 00:09:53,134
What was he looking for?

183
00:09:53,217 --> 00:09:55,303
How important are you?

184
00:09:57,388 --> 00:09:58,848
Do you think I'm a gossip?

185
00:09:58,931 --> 00:10:01,726
You know, if you want to know,
ask him yourself.

186
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:03,728
[in Cebuano] Whatever!

187
00:10:05,187 --> 00:10:06,522
Mh-mm.

188
00:10:06,606 --> 00:10:08,357
You two, huh? You already have secrets.

189
00:10:09,442 --> 00:10:12,653
But you know, you two are a good match.

190
00:10:12,737 --> 00:10:13,904
Huh?

191
00:10:13,988 --> 00:10:17,575
He's handsome, and you're beautiful.

192
00:10:18,534 --> 00:10:19,452
Perfect!

193
00:10:20,119 --> 00:10:23,331
You know that's impossible.

194
00:10:23,414 --> 00:10:25,875
I'm Muslim and he's Christian.

195
00:10:25,958 --> 00:10:27,293
How is that possible?

196
00:10:28,085 --> 00:10:31,881
So are you saying
that if someone converts,

197
00:10:31,964 --> 00:10:33,215
the two of you could be together?

198
00:10:33,299 --> 00:10:34,634
Come on!

199
00:10:34,717 --> 00:10:36,469
You know what, you're annoying!

200
00:10:36,552 --> 00:10:38,638
Nurse, this is for 126.

201
00:10:40,264 --> 00:10:42,433
Obviously,

202
00:10:42,516 --> 00:10:44,560
you're crushing on someone from TFA.

203
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:45,686
What's his name again?

204
00:10:46,270 --> 00:10:48,522
Andre! You have a crush on Andre, right?

205
00:10:50,107 --> 00:10:51,108
[chuckles]

206
00:10:52,860 --> 00:10:56,906
Wow, you're even pairing up
your names, huh!

207
00:10:56,989 --> 00:10:58,074
- Gracia…
- Jamilah--

208
00:10:58,157 --> 00:10:59,325
Andre…

209
00:10:59,408 --> 00:11:01,452
- Give that to me. So silly!
- You're unbelievable!

210
00:11:01,535 --> 00:11:02,870
- [chuckles]
- You two are so noisy.

211
00:11:02,953 --> 00:11:04,705
- Give it to me, please.
- Stop it already.

212
00:11:04,789 --> 00:11:06,999
- Oh! [laughs]
- Give it to me.

213
00:11:07,083 --> 00:11:09,210
[laughs]

214
00:11:09,293 --> 00:11:10,169
Hmm.

215
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:12,296
- There's your mother-in-law.
- [hits paper playfully]

216
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:13,547
Oh, sorry.

217
00:11:14,382 --> 00:11:15,591
She's here.

218
00:11:15,674 --> 00:11:17,176
Stop it.

219
00:11:17,259 --> 00:11:19,887
Dr. Teresa is here, be quiet.

220
00:11:19,970 --> 00:11:21,347
Hi, Doc!

221
00:11:21,430 --> 00:11:22,765
- [nurse] Good morning, Doc.
- Good morning.

222
00:11:22,848 --> 00:11:24,016
- Good morning!
- Good morning, Doc!

223
00:11:31,190 --> 00:11:34,944
General Villenueva
sends his congratulations to you.

224
00:11:35,694 --> 00:11:40,616
Because of you,
the public's trust in the police

225
00:11:40,699 --> 00:11:41,826
is slowly coming back.

226
00:11:43,035 --> 00:11:44,203
Thank you, sir.

227
00:11:45,037 --> 00:11:46,288
But that was a team effort.

228
00:11:46,372 --> 00:11:48,499
I wouldn't have succeeded in the operation

229
00:11:48,582 --> 00:11:51,627
without the help
of every member of Task Force Alpha.

230
00:11:51,710 --> 00:11:53,504
Of course.

231
00:11:53,587 --> 00:11:57,591
I'm very grateful
that my son came home safely.

232
00:11:59,009 --> 00:12:00,511
And more than that,

233
00:12:01,470 --> 00:12:02,721
thank you, Reyes,

234
00:12:02,805 --> 00:12:06,725
for reminding me why I chose this job.

235
00:12:06,809 --> 00:12:09,019
I want a safe world

236
00:12:09,103 --> 00:12:12,189
for my children
and my future grandchildren.

237
00:12:12,982 --> 00:12:14,567
We share the same belief, sir.

238
00:12:16,652 --> 00:12:19,113
For the country and for family.

239
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:24,160
Good.

240
00:12:27,079 --> 00:12:32,626
Well, now, focus on catching

241
00:12:32,710 --> 00:12:36,505
those who are selling illegal weapons
to minors.

242
00:12:36,589 --> 00:12:38,507
They need to be held accountable!

243
00:12:38,591 --> 00:12:41,552
[pensive music playing]

244
00:12:53,439 --> 00:12:54,815
What are you looking for?

245
00:12:55,316 --> 00:12:56,901
Is this what you're looking for?

246
00:13:01,864 --> 00:13:03,866
[Marcus] I have to see this case through.

247
00:13:05,034 --> 00:13:06,952
For kids like him.

248
00:13:09,914 --> 00:13:11,874
For kids like Gabriel.

249
00:13:13,792 --> 00:13:15,252
[Jalil] <i>As they say,</i>

250
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:19,590
when we lose loved ones,

251
00:13:22,051 --> 00:13:26,222
the pain never really goes away,
we just get used to it.

252
00:13:30,684 --> 00:13:33,812
- Doctor.
- Hey, Jamilah.

253
00:13:36,398 --> 00:13:37,983
Doctor, are you okay?

254
00:13:41,987 --> 00:13:43,531
I don't know, Jamilah.

255
00:13:43,614 --> 00:13:45,658
With everything happening right now,

256
00:13:46,367 --> 00:13:49,995
I can't help but keep worrying
about my children.

257
00:13:51,413 --> 00:13:53,624
I never thought that even now,

258
00:13:53,707 --> 00:13:57,294
Marcus still carries
Gabriel's favorite toy with him

259
00:13:57,378 --> 00:13:59,880
wherever he goes, even on his missions.

260
00:14:00,881 --> 00:14:04,593
Doctor, I know it's no secret to you that…

261
00:14:05,427 --> 00:14:08,055
I had bad feelings toward your son before.

262
00:14:09,890 --> 00:14:12,893
But when I got to know him,

263
00:14:12,977 --> 00:14:15,521
I understood what you meant back then.

264
00:14:16,564 --> 00:14:18,732
He's not…

265
00:14:19,567 --> 00:14:22,653
as bad as I thought he was.

266
00:14:23,279 --> 00:14:25,197
I understand you, Jamilah.

267
00:14:25,281 --> 00:14:29,577
And thank you for letting
my son prove himself.

268
00:14:30,244 --> 00:14:33,664
Sometimes you really need
to give a person a chance

269
00:14:33,747 --> 00:14:36,250
to truly know them.

270
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:38,878
That's what I always tell Marcus.

271
00:14:39,503 --> 00:14:42,464
He has a colleague
he doesn't get along with,

272
00:14:43,382 --> 00:14:46,051
Major Allan Espina.

273
00:14:46,135 --> 00:14:51,015
[tense music playing]

274
00:14:51,098 --> 00:14:55,269
But I'm sure they'll be okay eventually.

275
00:14:58,105 --> 00:15:01,859
Marcus told me that Allan was the one
who picked up your father.

276
00:15:05,070 --> 00:15:06,697
[Jamilah sobs]

277
00:15:07,239 --> 00:15:08,824
- [Jamilah] <i>Jalil!</i>
<i>- Jalil.</i>

278
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:12,369
[cries]

279
00:15:13,287 --> 00:15:15,456
- [Jamilah] <i>Father?</i>
- [sobs]

280
00:15:18,751 --> 00:15:22,212
[crying, sobbing]

281
00:15:22,296 --> 00:15:24,214
[tense music continues]

282
00:15:42,608 --> 00:15:44,568
Uh, yes, Doctor.

283
00:15:45,194 --> 00:15:49,281
I think Major Espina is a good person.

284
00:15:54,536 --> 00:15:56,163
Lately…

285
00:15:58,374 --> 00:16:01,502
I've been thinking of Gabriel
because of Allan.

286
00:16:03,712 --> 00:16:04,630
How so?

287
00:16:05,339 --> 00:16:08,050
I told him about Gabriel.

288
00:16:08,634 --> 00:16:10,594
And while I was talking to him,
it was like…

289
00:16:11,220 --> 00:16:13,639
Like I could see my son in him.

290
00:16:14,223 --> 00:16:18,519
If he was still alive,
he would probably be a police,

291
00:16:18,602 --> 00:16:22,064
just like Allan and his brother, Marcus.

292
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:27,361
By the way, how's your brother, Jalil?

293
00:16:29,446 --> 00:16:30,406
Um…

294
00:16:31,907 --> 00:16:35,160
We haven't spoken
or seen each other in a long time.

295
00:16:36,036 --> 00:16:38,247
You must be worried about him.

296
00:16:39,331 --> 00:16:41,583
I watched MMK's documentary,

297
00:16:42,334 --> 00:16:44,545
and I realized how much
you've gone through.

298
00:16:49,258 --> 00:16:51,176
Uh, by the way, doctor,

299
00:16:51,260 --> 00:16:54,179
I haven't thanked you properly.

300
00:16:54,763 --> 00:16:58,058
For operating on Jalil.

301
00:16:58,684 --> 00:16:59,935
Thank you.

302
00:17:00,019 --> 00:17:02,730
[morose music plays]

303
00:17:04,106 --> 00:17:06,108
[gasps, exhales]

304
00:17:07,317 --> 00:17:10,320
[Jalil] Doctor… thank you so much.

305
00:17:12,531 --> 00:17:16,952
And for not reporting him to the police.

306
00:17:17,953 --> 00:17:19,288
Thank you.

307
00:17:19,371 --> 00:17:23,042
Honestly, that was a dilemma for me.

308
00:17:24,376 --> 00:17:28,797
But I believed you were telling the truth
that Jalil isn't a criminal.

309
00:17:29,673 --> 00:17:33,802
Besides, I know Omar.
He's not the type to harbor a fugitive.

310
00:17:36,263 --> 00:17:38,390
- Thank you.
- Jamilah…

311
00:17:40,934 --> 00:17:44,980
Wherever Jalil is right now, don't worry.

312
00:17:46,607 --> 00:17:48,192
I'm praying for his safety.

313
00:17:50,778 --> 00:17:52,404
Thank you, doctor.

314
00:17:53,113 --> 00:17:58,285
[music builds]

315
00:18:01,872 --> 00:18:06,794
Gab Lozano got his gun from a gaming app

316
00:18:06,877 --> 00:18:07,878
called Cubix.

317
00:18:07,961 --> 00:18:10,339
He was contacted by an anonymous account

318
00:18:10,422 --> 00:18:12,716
with the username "Uncle Tony."

319
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:15,844
He was paying for the gun in installments.

320
00:18:15,928 --> 00:18:19,139
Wow. That means,
Gab was transferring 500 pesos

321
00:18:19,223 --> 00:18:21,266
from his allowance every Friday

322
00:18:21,350 --> 00:18:23,894
into this Uncle Tony's PesoLift account?

323
00:18:24,478 --> 00:18:27,523
Yes. Unfortunately,
that account's been deactivated,

324
00:18:27,606 --> 00:18:28,732
along with the phone number.

325
00:18:28,816 --> 00:18:30,234
That means,

326
00:18:31,235 --> 00:18:33,695
he only talked to the kid

327
00:18:33,779 --> 00:18:35,114
to influence him into committing violence.

328
00:18:37,449 --> 00:18:39,618
He's basically giving the gun away.

329
00:18:40,536 --> 00:18:42,121
Nobody pays for a gun in installments.

330
00:18:42,830 --> 00:18:45,207
[Usman] What kind of dealer would do that?

331
00:18:45,290 --> 00:18:50,546
If it's that cheap, it means
that the seller isn't after the money.

332
00:18:52,714 --> 00:18:56,927
They use the gaming app
to find a new kid to commit a crime.

333
00:18:59,763 --> 00:19:03,308
Those syndicates
who use high-powered firearms

334
00:19:03,392 --> 00:19:05,477
also acquire their weapons the same way.

335
00:19:07,604 --> 00:19:09,148
[gunfire]

336
00:19:10,858 --> 00:19:13,193
[explosion]

337
00:19:13,944 --> 00:19:15,904
- Nobody move!
- [people scream]

338
00:19:19,408 --> 00:19:21,410
They don't benefit from profits.

339
00:19:21,994 --> 00:19:23,787
They don't care about the money.

340
00:19:24,913 --> 00:19:27,916
- Their primary objective…
- Is to cause chaos.

341
00:19:28,917 --> 00:19:30,085
But why?

342
00:19:30,752 --> 00:19:35,257
[pensive music playing]

343
00:19:50,022 --> 00:19:51,940
[Ram] <i>My goodness!</i>

344
00:19:52,024 --> 00:19:54,318
<i>That Agent Marcus Reyes</i>
<i>is like a superhero!</i>

345
00:19:54,401 --> 00:19:56,653
<i>I saw that video of him</i>

346
00:19:56,737 --> 00:19:59,615
<i>saving the kid who almost</i>
<i>fell off the rooftop.</i>

347
00:19:59,698 --> 00:20:02,701
<i>It was incredible!</i>

348
00:20:02,784 --> 00:20:04,870
<i>The police have changed a lot</i>
<i>nowadays, huh?</i>

349
00:20:04,953 --> 00:20:08,415
<i>They're taking a more aggressive approach</i>
<i>in investigating the Cubix app.</i>

350
00:20:08,498 --> 00:20:11,418
Apparently, that is where
the illegal weapons

351
00:20:11,501 --> 00:20:13,545
that are sold to minors come from.

352
00:20:14,213 --> 00:20:17,090
I also heard the developers
have taken action.

353
00:20:17,174 --> 00:20:19,801
<i>They've temporarily removed</i>
<i>the chat feature of Cubix</i>

354
00:20:19,885 --> 00:20:22,012
<i>while the investigation is ongoing,</i>

355
00:20:22,095 --> 00:20:24,640
<i>to prevent smugglers from exploiting it.</i>

356
00:20:24,723 --> 00:20:27,017
And here's another big development!

357
00:20:27,100 --> 00:20:29,645
Due to the series of successful operations

358
00:20:29,728 --> 00:20:31,939
and restored stability,

359
00:20:32,022 --> 00:20:35,484
<i>Japanese investors</i>
<i>have responded positively as well.</i>

360
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:37,027
<i>Gosh, this looks like the start</i>

361
00:20:37,110 --> 00:20:41,740
<i>of renewed foreign investor confidence</i>
<i>in the Philippines.</i>

362
00:20:41,823 --> 00:20:44,993
<i>It seems the major investment deal</i>

363
00:20:45,077 --> 00:20:48,205
<i>scheduled for the conference</i>
<i>and official signing this week</i>

364
00:20:48,288 --> 00:20:49,915
<i>- is pushing through!</i>
- No…

365
00:20:50,832 --> 00:20:52,251
- This can't happen!
- [tablet thuds]

366
00:20:52,334 --> 00:20:56,046
[morose music playing]

367
00:21:04,137 --> 00:21:06,139
If our suspicions are correct,

368
00:21:06,223 --> 00:21:08,600
then that means everything
that's been happening here…

369
00:21:08,684 --> 00:21:10,143
They were all planned.

370
00:21:10,227 --> 00:21:12,980
Every incident
caused by the spread of illegal firearms

371
00:21:13,563 --> 00:21:15,274
- was deliberate.
- But what for?

372
00:21:16,358 --> 00:21:18,151
What do they gain from all this chaos?

373
00:21:18,235 --> 00:21:21,071
How does the syndicate benefit from it

374
00:21:21,154 --> 00:21:22,906
if they're not making money off it?

375
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:31,957
[dark music playing]

376
00:21:46,722 --> 00:21:52,436
[dark music continues]

377
00:21:52,519 --> 00:21:53,729
[music fades]

378
00:21:53,812 --> 00:21:56,773
Father, I've just returned
from our island.

379
00:21:57,774 --> 00:22:01,778
I found out there were armed men
causing trouble there.

380
00:22:02,404 --> 00:22:05,741
They were trying to steal
the weapons we buried there.

381
00:22:06,783 --> 00:22:08,785
But we were able to stop them.

382
00:22:09,786 --> 00:22:13,749
I taught our people
how to use those weapons

383
00:22:13,832 --> 00:22:16,501
so they could defend themselves.

384
00:22:17,419 --> 00:22:20,088
And so no one
would ever threaten our island again.

385
00:22:21,631 --> 00:22:24,509
You did the right thing, Jalil.

386
00:22:25,010 --> 00:22:27,429
We can't let
what happened before happen again.

387
00:22:27,512 --> 00:22:32,893
[brooding music playing]

388
00:22:43,779 --> 00:22:46,031
[glasses clink]

389
00:22:47,407 --> 00:22:48,950
I wish I'd done it sooner.

390
00:22:50,952 --> 00:22:54,289
I should have allowed them
to use the guns.

391
00:22:55,248 --> 00:22:57,709
I should've prepared them sooner.

392
00:22:58,835 --> 00:23:02,380
Things wouldn't have ended up
being so bad.

393
00:23:02,464 --> 00:23:06,384
Jalil, don't blame yourself.

394
00:23:07,219 --> 00:23:08,720
It's not your fault.

395
00:23:08,804 --> 00:23:11,973
You only followed what I taught you.

396
00:23:12,057 --> 00:23:13,892
Ever since you were a child,

397
00:23:15,310 --> 00:23:17,354
I've always reminded you

398
00:23:17,979 --> 00:23:23,026
that peace should come before war

399
00:23:24,152 --> 00:23:25,445
and violence.

400
00:23:27,823 --> 00:23:29,032
But…

401
00:23:30,242 --> 00:23:32,911
there are people
who are violent by nature.

402
00:23:33,662 --> 00:23:35,872
No matter how much we prepared,

403
00:23:37,499 --> 00:23:39,960
we couldn't have stopped what happened.

404
00:23:40,043 --> 00:23:44,631
[grim music playing]

405
00:23:51,972 --> 00:23:53,306
They're working together.

406
00:23:53,390 --> 00:23:54,808
They're figuring things out.

407
00:23:55,392 --> 00:23:57,519
All they have right now are suspicions.

408
00:23:58,186 --> 00:24:00,105
So you're still safe.

409
00:24:00,188 --> 00:24:01,189
For now!

410
00:24:01,273 --> 00:24:04,943
But what happens when they find evidence?
When they learn the truth?

411
00:24:05,527 --> 00:24:06,987
Then I'll just kill them all.

412
00:24:07,070 --> 00:24:08,446
[Lara scoffs]

413
00:24:08,530 --> 00:24:10,073
Are you crazy?

414
00:24:10,157 --> 00:24:11,700
Is killing people
all you ever think about?

415
00:24:11,783 --> 00:24:13,994
Marcus is all over the headlines
right now.

416
00:24:14,077 --> 00:24:15,328
If anything happens to him,

417
00:24:15,412 --> 00:24:16,663
this will all blow up.

418
00:24:17,664 --> 00:24:19,541
Madam, I'm just saying--

419
00:24:19,624 --> 00:24:21,668
Shut up! I don't even want to hear it.

420
00:24:21,751 --> 00:24:22,752
That Espina…

421
00:24:22,836 --> 00:24:24,296
We don't even know where he's from,

422
00:24:24,379 --> 00:24:27,215
who sent him here,
or who he's reporting to.

423
00:24:27,299 --> 00:24:29,968
We don't know if he's working
for someone powerful.

424
00:24:30,051 --> 00:24:31,303
[huffs]

425
00:24:31,386 --> 00:24:33,471
If anything happens,

426
00:24:33,555 --> 00:24:36,266
we don't want any attention
to zero in on us.

427
00:24:36,349 --> 00:24:41,271
[unsettling music playing]

428
00:24:47,235 --> 00:24:52,616
[dark music playing]

429
00:24:52,699 --> 00:24:53,783
[clears throat]

430
00:24:57,329 --> 00:24:58,580
Do you know what you're going to do?

431
00:24:58,663 --> 00:24:59,873
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

432
00:25:00,498 --> 00:25:01,499
Are you sure?

433
00:25:01,583 --> 00:25:02,751
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

434
00:25:03,376 --> 00:25:06,588
Have your families already left
for another country?

435
00:25:06,671 --> 00:25:08,173
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

436
00:25:08,256 --> 00:25:11,551
What you're about to do
is crucial to our goal.

437
00:25:12,177 --> 00:25:13,929
But don't worry.

438
00:25:14,012 --> 00:25:15,722
Before any verdict
is handed down against you,

439
00:25:16,431 --> 00:25:17,724
we will have won.

440
00:25:17,807 --> 00:25:19,351
The fight will already be over.

441
00:25:19,434 --> 00:25:21,895
The power will be ours.

442
00:25:22,646 --> 00:25:24,231
Prepare yourselves.

443
00:25:24,314 --> 00:25:26,399
Over the next few days,

444
00:25:26,483 --> 00:25:28,526
the evidence pointing to you will surface.

445
00:25:30,153 --> 00:25:31,196
Gentlemen.

446
00:25:31,780 --> 00:25:34,950
We will never forget your sacrifices.

447
00:25:35,033 --> 00:25:37,535
[dark music continues]

448
00:25:43,333 --> 00:25:44,334
[chuckles]

449
00:25:45,460 --> 00:25:46,670
- Cheers.
- Yeah.

450
00:26:04,854 --> 00:26:09,901
Mustapha already has Datu Rahman!

451
00:26:09,985 --> 00:26:15,031
Who knows what information
Mustapha will get from him?

452
00:26:15,115 --> 00:26:17,826
Brother, let's live in truth.

453
00:26:17,909 --> 00:26:19,953
<i>Tell that to your children.</i>

454
00:26:20,036 --> 00:26:21,621
Why did you get into this line of work?

455
00:26:21,705 --> 00:26:23,707
Because I want to help people
who can't defend themselves.

456
00:26:23,790 --> 00:26:25,792
[Marcus] <i>My life needs to have meaning</i>

457
00:26:25,875 --> 00:26:28,628
so that losing my brother
won't be in vain.

458
00:26:28,712 --> 00:26:30,255
Marcus's brother went missing?

459
00:26:30,338 --> 00:26:32,465
I'm adopted. Could I be Gabriel?

460
00:26:32,549 --> 00:26:34,926
[man] <i>I've traced the IP address</i>
<i>of the user account</i>

461
00:26:35,010 --> 00:26:36,803
<i>- "Uncle Tony."</i>
- Buddy.

462
00:26:36,886 --> 00:26:38,555
[Azuelo] <i>How are we supposed</i>
<i>to fix this now?</i>

463
00:26:38,638 --> 00:26:42,309
Whoever uploaded that video
is the one sabotaging us.

464
00:26:42,392 --> 00:26:45,103
Allies shouldn't keep secrets.

465
00:26:45,186 --> 00:26:46,771
The video is real.

466
00:26:46,855 --> 00:26:47,814
[Lara] <i>Because of you, Marcus,</i>

467
00:26:47,897 --> 00:26:49,733
I lost my chance to avenge my parents.

468
00:26:49,816 --> 00:26:52,027
[Marcus] <i>They're trying to silence me.</i>

469
00:26:52,110 --> 00:26:53,945
<i>I will soon find out the truth.</i>

470
00:26:54,029 --> 00:26:56,072
[Felix] <i>Get along with Task Force Alpha</i>

471
00:26:56,156 --> 00:26:58,283
<i>because they're the ones</i>
<i>you need to manipulate.</i>

472
00:26:58,366 --> 00:27:00,118
[Lara] <i>If Agent Reyes trusts you,</i>

473
00:27:00,201 --> 00:27:01,786
then I'm willing to work with you too.

474
00:27:01,870 --> 00:27:03,538
[Jalil] <i>Turns out we want the same thing.</i>
